{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/34/comments/56120621.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake:b2cf0bbda015..aff4ec366564?path=cmake%2FFindOptiX.cmake"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/34/_/diff#comment-56120621"}}, "parent": {"id": 56120491, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/34/comments/56120491.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/34/_/diff#comment-56120491"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 34, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/34.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/34"}}, "title": "Add FindOptiX.cmake"}, "content": {"raw": "Just keep in mind that find-modules called by `find_package(~)` have their own scoping rules, which are not necessarily the same rules as `add_subdirectory(~)` or `include(~)`. So when you test the scope, be sure to put the macro in a find-module that you invoke with `find_package(~)`.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Just keep in mind that find-modules called by <code>find_package(~)</code> have their own scoping rules, which are not necessarily the same rules as <code>add_subdirectory(~)</code> or <code>include(~)</code>. So when you test the scope, be sure to put the macro in a find-module that you invoke with <code>find_package(~)</code>.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-02-13T01:16:17.833245+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c9%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.p